Polylactic Acid (PLA) is segmented based on type, application, and end-use industry. In terms of type, PLA includes Poly L-lactic Acid (PLLA), Poly D-lactic Acid (PDLA), and Poly DL-lactic Acid (PDLLA). Each type has its unique properties and applications within the market. When it comes to application, PLA finds its uses in packaging, textiles, electronics, and medical sectors. The eco-friendly nature of PLA makes it a preferred choice in various sustainable applications. Furthermore, in the end-use industry segment, PLA is extensively used in packaging, automotive, medical, and agriculture industries due to its biodegradable and compostable nature.

